BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gZVcdrNmCFsRaZJpUYSFj
SUMMARY:Improv Happy Hour
DTSTAMP:20260406T013621Z
DTSTART:20260405T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Improv Happy Hour—where comedy is unscripted\, unpr
	edictable\, and unbelievably fun! From movie mashups to literary spoofs an
	d bold\, experimental comedy\, our quick-thinking performers turn your sug
	gestions into hilarious scenes on the spot. This family-friendly show at t
	he iconic Gum Wall in Pike Place Market guarantees a night of laughter\, s
	urprises\, and improv magic you won’t forget. Bring your wildest ideas\, y
	our loudest laughs\, and get ready for a one-of-a-kind comedy experience—b
	ecause at Improv Happy Hour\, anything can happen (and usually does)! Buy 
	Tickets\n\nhttps://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-ho
	ur-2/?occurrence=2026-04-05\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-hour-2/?oc
	currence=2026-04-05
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:85L666xFZIJmhixvbXrh8
SUMMARY:THIS IS FOR YOU: An Improvised Theatre Poetry Experience
DTSTAMP:20260406T013621Z
DTSTART:20260405T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Step into a world where your memories spark the unexpected\, yo
	ur objects tell untold stories\, and your life becomes art in motion. With
	 a swirl of spontaneous theater\, hand-typed poetry\, and the soulful soun
	ds of live musicians on stage each night unfolds like a dream—unrepeatable
	\, electric\, and uniquely yours. One moment\, you're laughing at a scene 
	born from a trinket in your pocket\; the next\, a poem crafted just for yo
	u finds its way into your hands. This is poetry in motion. This is music i
	n the moment. This is theater made from the fabric of your life. Come laug
	h. Come cry. Come as you are. ✨ THIS IS FOR YOU! ✨ Don’t miss this once-in
	-a-lifetime fusion of words\, sound\, and improvisation. April is the mont
	h of poetry—come celebrate the magic! Get Tickets\n\nhttps://www.pikeplace
	market.org/events-calendar/this-is-for-you-an-improvised-theatre-poetry-ex
	perience/?occurrence=2026-04-05\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/this-is-for-you-an-impr
	ovised-theatre-poetry-experience/?occurrence=2026-04-05
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MFlyoTgeP2splgeas8JoC
SUMMARY:Medusa Quartet - genre-defying chamber-folk ensemble
DTSTAMP:20260406T013621Z
DTSTART:20260405T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Named after one of mythology’s most misunderstood figures\\\, t
	he Medusa Quartet channels the power of transformation\\\, reclaiming what
	 was once feared and turning it into something fiercely magical. Saskia To
	mkins – Violin\\\, Viola\\\, Cello\\\, Nyckelharpa\; Marta Solek – Suka\\\
	, Plock Fiddle\\\, Cello\; Lea Kirstein – Violin\\\, Viola\\\, Cello\; Geo
	rgia Hathaway – Violin\\\, Vocals – A genre-defying chamber-folk quartet t
	hat fuses centuries-old string traditions with contemporary storytelling a
	nd original compositions.  Medusa’s dynamic arrangement style cross-pollin
	ates the sounds of Middle Eastern\\\, Scandinavian\\\, Celtic\\\, Appalach
	ian\\\, and Eastern European music\\\, as well as original tunes\\\, to cr
	eate something previously unheard. The dynamic band connects audiences acr
	oss dividing lines of culture and identity to reveal the common threads be
	neath. Join us for a very special concert! \\nDoors open at 6:30 pm for th
	e 7:00 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (lower Brick Buil
	ding). \\nTickets are available in advance online\\\, in-person at prior S
	FS concerts\\\, or at the door.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/med
	usa-quartet-genre-defying-chamber-folk-ensemble/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborh
	ood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/medusa-quartet-genre-defying-chambe
	r-folk-ensemble/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
